  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Towards creating sustainable market linkages and initiating value addition on fruits and vegetables</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">BHAG: To establish the first farmer owned juice factory in Ethiopia
Gamo Gofa Farmers Vegetable  Fruit Marketing Cooperative Union PLC (GGCU). The union is located in the city center of Arba Minch town  Gamu Gofa Zone  SNNP-Region. The union has a lot of fruit and vegetable production potential especially banana  mango  Apple etc. in the union working area more than four hundred thousand tons per year produced. The has been Agriterra client since January 2017.  The union has been engaged in the marketing activities of banana  apple and manage fruits. Although the union have an enormous production potential  the union only collect and sells 5-7% of their members&apos; produces. In the fruit and vegetable value chain brokers have strong influence and dominate the market. Hence  for the past years most of the farmers at Gamo Gofa union have been highly exploited by brokers and local traders and they are selling their fruits with low price. The farmers are always the price taker&apos;s not a decider.  In the bigger cities like Addis Ababa  the price for fruits and vegetables are becoming too high. This is mainly emanated because of a very length value chain and presence of too many actors/brokers in this chain.</narrative>
  </description>
  <description type="4">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">In 2017 action plan  Agriterra has able to create awareness for the Gamo Gofa union board member and management about the importance of bringing a breakthrough change in their making outlets and marketing system  capacitated the union management and board about financial management and improved the union relationship with its primary cooperatives. In addition  two direct market linkage (with Nigat consumer cooperatives and Fresh Corner supermarket) both found in Addis Ababa. These linkages are innovative and have dual benefits: The transaction costs will be less by avoiding too many actors in the value chain which leads a lesser price for consumers and for Gamo Gofa it has created a reliable and sustainable market. But still more effort should be exerted to assist the Union further to be very competent in the fruit and vegetable value chain.
In 2018 year  we will further create a sustainable market  improve the union equity capital  professionalize the union financial management by installing sage 50 software  install internal control mechanism and initiate value addition on fruits.</narrative>
  </description>
  <description type="2">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Strengthening the union management and board competencesConducting feasibility study on fruit value additionCreating 3 sustainable market linkagesMobilizing 1.02 million ETB equity capital from membersProfessionalize the union financial management by installing sage 50 software</narrative>
  </description>
